Constructor Detail

FedoraAppBatchIngestController

public FedoraAppBatchIngestController(TransformMetaData XSLTransformer,
                                      java.lang.String institution,
                                      java.lang.String batchSet,
                                      java.lang.String fedoraContext,
                                      BatchIngestOptions batchOptions)
                               throws FatalException
Create a new FedoraAppBatchIngestController for an individual batch set.

Parameters:
XSLTransformer - Performs the XSLT to transform input XML to FOXML.
institution - The institution name for the batch set (ie codu).
batchSet - The name of this batch set (ie ectd or frid) (Used to name reports).
fedoraContext - The context used by fedora when creating the fedora objects unique identifier (PID) This context must already be known by fedora (specified in fedora.fcfg) This is usually the same as the institution name (ie codu).
batchOptions - Options for running this batch set (in a web environment this is obtained from a web form)
Throws:
FatalException - thrown to stop execution of batch set.

getAdministratorUsingProgramProperiesFileCredentials

public static Administrator getAdministratorUsingProgramProperiesFileCredentials()
                                                                          throws FatalException
Get THE SINGLETON REMOTE TASK ingest administrator, THERE IS ONLY ONE, if it does not exist this function will create it.. This is a method to get a fedora administrator using the settings in the program properties file (batchIngest.properites). This is a different administrator then the one used for manual ingests if System properties javax.net.ssl.trustStore or javax.net.ssl.trustStorePassword are not set, they are set to "\\fedora\\client\\truststore" and "tomcat" respectively.

Returns:
a loged in fedora aministrator
Throws:
FatalException

registerHandle

public static boolean registerHandle(java.lang.String pid)
                              throws FatalException
Connects with the ADR and requests a handle to be assigned from handle.net for a specific PID. Note: The handle is the URL with the pid. We don't recieve anything back.

NOTE: Looks for BATCH_INGEST_DISABLE_GET_HANDLE in the application propertites file, if set return true without attempting to obtain a handle.

Parameters:
pid -
Returns:
true if a handle was assigned
Throws:
FatalException - if unable to assign handle.
See Also:
FedoraAppConstants.BATCH_INGEST_DISABLE_GET_HANDLE_PROPERTY
